This movie was done in a very tasteful decent way and matched my expectations as did Part one - "What Would You Do For Love". Kids and Grandma safe. No profanity or buffoonery! This is perfect for a viewing with company or any relatives over the holidays. The plot was lively as were the character development. Each of the main characters were all articulate and could be understood. It was reminiscent of "Let's Stay Together" tv show.  It was low budget set however it represented well and I had no ill-conceived notions about the character backgrounds. They also demonstrated how I wish more people were in film and real-life by talking out issues with another. A+ for communication. I'm familiar with the work of Carl Payne, Christian Keyes, Jason Weaver and of course Gabby Dennis and Vanessa Simmons. My only critique in this film would be they should have left the Kevin "Heart" segment out. In real life 100 people would "NOT" have been duped and not looked closer at the spelling of the performers name on their purchased tickets. All in all - a decent flick. Take note low budget film makers...this is how it's done.
